This article describes the '''localization''' (abbreviated '''L10N''') and '''internationalization''' (abbreviated '''I18N''') of software.

== System ==

=== Locale ===
{{InfoBox stack
|{{InfoBox wikipedia|Locale|header=true}}
}}
A locale defines settings such as the language, the date/time format and the paper size that are used in a certain country. You can find possible locales in {{Path|/usr/share/i18n/locales}}. E.g. for Germany choose ''<code>de-DE.UTF-8</code>''. A UTF-8 based locale is strongly recommended.

==== Kernel ====
You need to activate the following kernel options:
{{Kernel||<pre>
File Systems -->
  Native Language Support -->
    (utf8) Default NLS Option
    <*> NLS UTF8
</pre>}}

==== Generate locales ====
Add your locales to {{Path|/etc/locale.gen}} (optional: delete all other locales):
{{File|/etc/locale.gen||<pre>
de_DE.UTF-8 UTF-8
</pre>}}
Afterwards run '''locale-gen''' to generate the locales. '''locale -a''' lists all installed locales.

==== Use locales ====
Use '''eselect locale''' or manually add your locale to {{Path|/etc/env.d/02locale}} so the system uses the locale:
{{File|/etc/env.d/02locale||<pre>
LANG="de_DE.UTF-8"
LC_COLLATE="C"
</pre>}}

To apply the changes run:
{{RootCmd
|env-update
|source /etc/profile
}}

'''locale''' now shows your locale.

==== USE flag ====
Portage knows the global USE flag ''nls'' for enabling support for localization in other packages (default for almost all [[profile]]s). Also set the ''LINGUAS'' variable to support only your languages, e.g. for German:
{{File|/etc/portage/make.conf||<pre>
USE="... nls ..."
LINGUAS="de de_DE"
</pre>}}

A list of locales that can be used is provided as {{Path|/usr/portage/profiles/desc/linguas.desc}}:
{{Cmd|grep -i german /usr/portage/profiles/desc/linguas.desc|output=<pre>
de - German locale
de_DE - German locale for Germany
de_FR - German locale for France
</pre>}}

After setting this you want to update your system so the changes take effect:
{{Emerge|params+=--changed-use --deep|@world}}

=== Console font ===
Set the font used by the console. Valid values can be found in {{Path|/usr/share/consolefonts}}.

Set your console font in {{Path|/etc/conf.d/consolefont}}, e.g. for German:
{{File|/etc/conf.d/consolefont||<pre>
CONSOLEFONT="lat9w-16"
</pre>}}

=== Keyboard layout ===
Set the keyboard layout used by the console. Valid values can be found in {{Path|/usr/share/keymaps/YOUR_ARCH}}.

Set your keyboard layout in {{Path|/etc/conf.d/keymaps}}, e.g. for German:
{{File|/etc/conf.d/keymaps||<pre>
KEYMAP="de-latin1"
</pre>}}

=== Timezone ===
Set the timezone used at your location. Valid values can be found in {{Path|/usr/share/zoneinfo}}.

Set your timezone, e.g. for Germany:
{{RootCmd|cp /usr/share/zoneinfo/Europe/Berlin /etc/localtime}}

Next change your {{Path|/etc/timezone}} to the same timezone:
{{File|/etc/timezone||<pre>
Europe/Berlin
</pre>}}

